content.description: Sit start to the left of the arete near the alcove that harbors Fun Ladder. Climb into the finger crack and top out.
content.location: This route sits with a group of problems that are near the big crack in an alcove with a knee height, flat-topped boulder right by it. Refer to the map for a visual.

content.description: Same start as The Wiz, but continue out to the left and up on good edges.
content.location: Start as per the wiz, refer to the map if needed.

content.description: Make a high step onto a rail on the slab, and continue up to the top on some very small edges. This climb is great practice for slab anywhere!
content.protection: Pad/Spotter, watch your ankles on the landing
content.location: Just to the right of Pimp My Ride, on the slabbiest face on the boulder.

content.description: Starts on the large edge of the arête, up to a top right sloper and a high up left edge over the top.
content.location: Across the trail from the main boulder.

content.description: This stand start takes you up the right side of the arête
content.location: around the corner to the right of the slab face.

content.description: A very cool route on the main boulder at the Thompson Farm. Start on a pretty juggy sloping hold and throw up left to another jug, from here match your heel to your right hand on the sloper and rock over to some side pulls out to the right.  Easy top out, and a super fun problem!
content.location: Located on a bulge on the back side of the boulder, it is best identified by the first two holds, which are a sloping jug to match on, and then a large left hand jug/pinch that is thrown to.

content.description: Left side of the arête.
content.location: This climb is immediately to the right of Crackle, and tops out at the same spot.

content.description: Stand start on great feet and a solid left hand. find some friction with your right hand and work up the obvious line diagonal right to a solid jug. Next move is the top out.
content.location: This route is in the middle of the face, with the most obvious route features reaching up to the highest point.

content.description: Start low on the arete to the right of Friction fiction and make one pop move to the top of the boulder.
content.location: This route is located on the smaller main boulder with some easier slab climbs on it. Start to the Right of Friction Fiction and head up the small arete.

content.description: Start same as Redemption, but travel right to the feature and around into the corner to a crimp that is right above the crack. Getting into the crack with the right beta is not bad but with bad beta, this could be the crux and is where the landing is the worse. From here go down the large crack and out right onto some good side pulls. Get higher feet and throw for a sloper and match to completer the route (crux). If you top out add at least 1 grade maybe 2.
content.protection: At least two pads and a spotter
content.location: On the backside of the boulder. Start at Redemption and top out by Palm Reader.

content.description: Someone, please correct me if this is already a route, but you start to the left of Man Handle with left hand on a side pull crimp and right hand on a nice jug with a standing start (I also use a toe hook for my right foot). then traverse right and up for a tricky top out similar to Man Handle. The start is a bit sketchy but altogether a very fun route.
content.protection: Pad and spotter, first move has a higher consequence if you fall.
content.location: To the left of the big feature (Man Handle) on the backside of the boulder

content.description: Sit start to the right of Palm Reader, and cruise up the arete.
content.location: Just right of Palm Reader, on the arete, to the left of the hard and thin slabs.

content.description: Start on a good sidepull just right of the Dark Slot, mellower moves will lead into a hard sloping top out.
content.location: Just to the right of The Dark Slot on the face.

content.description: Sit start atop a boulder. Grab the sloping rail and continue up on progressively more positive holds, shuffling your feet up for an exciting mantle at the end.
content.location: To the left of the wide crack that harbors The Dark Slot there is a boulder - This problem starts sitting on top of that boulder and climbs the large boulder that harbors most of the routes here.

content.description: Starting just to the right of Fun Ladder, use a pinch with the left hand to gain some awful feet and a high gaston continue up and right into a scoop for an exciting finish
content.location: Just right of Fun Ladder. See map for details.

content.description: Start low and right of Shorty, slap up the lip on sloping holds until you reach Shorty, then top out.
content.location: Just to the right of Shorty on the small boulder that has easy slabs on the back.

content.description: This super awesome route takes a hard line up the face to the right of the Wiz (left of Fun Ladder). Start sitting (you'll probably be sitting on the knee-height block) and utilize some funky crimps to reach a couple of decent edges before you set your feet high and try to catch the elusive lip of the boulder. Hard and fun problem for sure!
content.protection: Pad & Spotter recommend - that block comes up quickly when you take the plunge!
content.location: This route is located in the alcove with Fun Ladder, on the slightly overhanging face. Refer to the map if needed.

content.description: Climb from The Wiz, into Lunge or Plunge. Adds some length to Lunge or Plunge, and seemingly ups the difficulty.
content.location: Located on the Wiz's start, climb around and into Lunge or Plunge

content.description: A super fun V0! Style your way up the right side of the wide crack that is "The Crack". While the climbing is not particularly interesting, there is a definite feeling of joy that comes with doing this problem.
content.location: Just to the right of The Crack, reference the map if needed.

content.description: Sit start to the right of Fireball on a small right facing flake and head up to the top of the boulder on what little you find for holds.
content.location: This route is located on the smaller main boulder with some easier slab climbs on it. Start to the right of Fireball and work your way to the top.

content.description: Stand start up a left hand side pull.
content.location: On the small boulder to the right of French Toast.

content.description: Begin this climb in down in the ditch in front of the main boulder. Climb the left side of the wide crack with some lie-back moves working up to a solid   hold near to top deep in the crack. From here work your way left out of the crack and over the rock below in front of the boulder to some good jug holds. Slap/mantle out up and over for the top out.
content.protection: Pad(s), Good Spotter(s). A fall near the beginning could get ugly.
content.location: This climb starts side of the rock facing the approach trail, on the left side of the obvious wide crack. climb down into the space between the boulders.

content.description: Crawl into the wide crack next to Dolph's Traverse (to the left) and Palm Reader ( to the right), then utilize squeeze chimney or off-width techniques to huff and puff your way to the top.
content.protection: Pad/Spotter, but you're probably not falling out of there.
content.location: The wide crack between Dolph's Traverse and Palm Reader.

content.description: Fun if you like wide cracks! Securely wiggle your way up the big crack in the alcove.
content.location: This is the wide crack between Fun Ladder and Lunge or Plunge.
This is the left most climb worth pointing out on the boulder.

content.description:
This variation adds a few great moves to Black Magic and tops out around the corner on the tallest point of the boulder, making an already-excellent problem truly superb. 

  Start as for White/Black Magic, work right past the crack to a rail just above the lip of the roof, then continue rightward to holds at the lip and feet on tiny edges. Gaston or cross into a layback on the left-facing crack, then reach around the prow to the right facing crack. Work your feet up, make a big move to the lip of the boulder, and float the chill but high topout. 

  Feels about as hard as Magician, which to me is solid V6. Both of these problems would be sought-after classics if they were at Pawtuckaway.
content.protection: Good idea to bring at least two pads, one for the traverse and one for the topout. As with most problems here, the landing is mostly nice and flat.

content.description: Climb just the left arete of The Dark Slot to the top for an exciting top out.
content.protection: Pad/Spotter, watch your head if you fall off the top!
content.location: Just left of The Dark Slot on it's arete.

content.description: Start the same way you would for White Magic. Instead of going straight up head out right towards a crack, and continue up that to the top.
content.location: Same start as White Magic, but it trends right.

content.description:
There are multiple boulders here. Great rock offering a little bit of something for everyone. The boulders are in the trees, but open enough to see ample sunlight throughout the day to keep the rock dry.   

    The land is owned and managed by UNH and abuts Foss Farm and college woods at the far NE end.
